    "summary": "Carmela was born in Italy and grew up in France from the age of nine months. Living in The Netherlands since many years,  she considers herself a true European. Through her  individual and professional experiences as a lecturer first and  later on as a manager in  international education and services, she became a global citizen and the world is her marketplace.. \n\nCarmela has expertise and advises in :\n\n-  Interim management in education \n-  Interim management and change management \n-  Procesmanagement and lean implementation in education\n-  Strategy development in internationalization of knowledge institutions + implementation\n-  Quality management  (ISO 9001: 2008, EPAS, EQUIS proof) and trainings in education\n-  Setting up an international office and its processes in (higher)education\n-  Coaching culture change processes in (higher) education \n-  (International) Partner search and recruiting policy/strategy in international education\n-  (International) interdisciplinary curriculum development in higher education (Minors) \n-  Teaching French and creating links between France and The Netherlands\n-  Intercultural awareness trainings in businesses and knowledge institutions\n-  Linking Education Network with Businesses and Entrepreneurs\n-  French Language and culture trainings in-company\n\nHer goals are:\n\n-  To link education to local businesses and industry \n-  To facilitate and stimulate cross-cultural experiences and interdisciplinarity\n-  To develop local networks for international strategies in education and businesses\n\n\nHer Specialties are:  Consultancy, Project Management, Interim Management:\n\n- Interim management \n- Quality Assurance and Auditing \n- Process management\n- International exchange in (Higher)Education worldwide\n- International Relations Management\n- Managing international projects and exchange of staff/scholars\n- Cross-cultural knowledge and experience, diversity issues\n- Recruiting and marketing policy in international education",
